==English==
===Pronunciation===
:plaj' ee o klaze

===Etymology===
:plageo, Greek "oblique" + klao, Greek "I cleave"

===Noun===
#A group of [[feldspar]] minerals that form a [[solid solution]] series from albite (sodium aluminum silicate) to anorthite (calcium aluminum silicate). The plagioclase feldspars are found in [[igneous]], [[plutonic]], and [[metamorphic]] [[rock]]s. They all have the triclinic-pinacoidal [[crystal]] habit, but only Albite commonly occurs in well crystallized specimens.


